roadmap
=======

A few honest notes about where simd-agent is going. Plans change as we
learn from real users and contributors — direction, not contract.

Day-to-day work tracking is on GitHub Milestones; for ideas open an
issue with the "roadmap" label.


soon
----

  - CLI client — `simd run` for humans, end-to-end from a terminal.
  - Broader self-healing — diagnoser reads step-by-step OpenFOAM logs.
  - More turbulence models — SA-DES, k-ω SST low-Re, transition.
  - Multiphase out of experimental — promote interFoam family.
  - Pre-built simulation templates — pipe, mixing tee, heat exchanger.


later
-----

  - Headless SDK — Python / TS bindings for batch sims and CI/CD.
  - Benchmarks suite — reference cases with agent-vs-specialist setup time.
  - Digital-twin streaming — live sensor feed as a prediction surface.
  - More LLM providers — Claude, OpenAI, local Llama.
  - Web-based mesh editor — parametric, in-browser.


maybe
-----

  - RL over the run loop — supplements rule-driven self-healing.
  - Optimisation loop — DoE / gradient-free over geometry.
  - Surrogate models — trained on high-fidelity simulation data.


how to influence the roadmap
----------------------------

  - Open a GitHub issue with the "roadmap" label.
  - Build it and open a PR — we prioritise aligned work.
  - Sponsor specific items if you want them pulled forward.
